name: 1K Arri Fresnel  (1)
notes:
The Arri 1K (1000w) Fresnel is an updated version of the Compact Series of Location Fresnels. Combining research, feedback from around the world and advances in technology, Arri has designed a series of six Fresnels with over 30 improvements for studio and location lighting. The True Blue Series has reduced weight, compact size and maximum light output. Arri's cross cooling system reduces lamp housing temperature by 25% and lens temperature by 17%. With special air channels built into the aluminum extrusion, a constant stream of air passes around the Fresnel lens and into the lamp head regardless of the tilt angle.

Bulb - EGT 1000W
120 or 240 volt use, AC or DC

This fixture will provide a 2.8' (0.9 m) diameter beam of 409 fc from a distance of 20' (6.1 m) at full spot. At full flood (same distance) it will provide a 48 fc, 20.4' (6.2 m) diameter beam. Laser-cut hexagonal safety mesh lets out more light and is tough enough to withstand location abuse.

name: 1K Molepar (1)
notes:
This is a multi-purpose 1000 watt single Par Head for studio, location or remote use. Diffuse and Specular Intensifiers are available for boosting the light output, as well as different bulbs, both 3200° and 5000° Kelvin.


Combining the Specular Intensifier (2275) and a very narrow spot par bulb, a beam of 900 footcandles 4.4 x 3 feet, at a distance of 15 feet may be achieved.

Using a wide flood par bulb with no intensifier will result in a beam of 52 footcandles 26 x 13.7 feet, at a distance of 15 feet.

Accepts different bulbs with built-in reflectors that disperse or internsify the light beam emitted from the head. May be used as a hanging, grid or pipe mounted fixture, or mounted on a light stand. Bulb may be rotated for hortizontal or vertical oval beam projection.

Bulbs - Sylvania / Osram FFS (1000W / 120V) PAR 64 Wide Flood Halogen Incandescent Lamp
            Sylvania / Osram FFN (1000W / 120V) Par 64 VNSP Lamp

name: 1K Nook Light (1)
notes:
This 1000W unit is primarily designed to fit into wall corners, small nooks or on ceilings. Also makes great work-lights, and background accents. Equipped with safety screen. Compact size. 

Bulb - FCM 1000W

Has dozens of applications where lighting in tight or confined areas presents a problem. Unit uses lamps from 1000 watt to 300 watts.

name: 1K Softlite (1)
notes:
The Mole Richardson 1K Softlite provides soft, diffused virtually shadowless light with a smooth field. Used for soft fill in commercial photography of products where shadows must be at a minimum. Also used in motion picture and television studios where shadows may be "washed out". Light is unobstructed when functioning. 

Bulb - FCM 1000W

Designed so that all the light comes indirect and unobstructed from diffused surfaces through an 18 x 18" (45.7 x 45.7 cm) aperture.

name: 1X2 Wooden Cucoloris (1)
notes:
The Cucoloris is used to create shadow patterns on backgrounds or subjects. A flatly lit wall can be broken up into interesting pools of light and shadow. Lighting directors frequently use them to simulate sunlight filtering through trees.

The Wood "cookie" creates a distinctive pattern. The pattern itself depends on the distance of the light source and the distance to the background.
